These are the lines I would keep even if the rest of the page disappeared.
&ldquo;The first 5 years of graduation, you have to be in as many different roles and industries and around people as possible.&rdquo;
&ldquo;During your 20s, have fun. That&rsquo;s what it&rsquo;s for. But at the same time, expose yourself to different opportunities that are out there.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I wouldn&rsquo;t change it at all.&rdquo;
&ldquo;People, right. Most people don&rsquo;t know how to manage people.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I see a lot of people have favoritism.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Everyone is equal. I don&rsquo;t care if you&rsquo;re the garbage man. I don&rsquo;t care if you&rsquo;re a CMO.&rdquo;
&ldquo;There&rsquo;s three levels in life: roots, trees, and forest.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Spend time with the ones you love.&rdquo;
